f=Brand Studio/weave/custom/brand-story-arcs/SKILL.md · in=brand-story-arcs makes brand's story *cumulative*. businesses tell new story campaign one plausible, none them adding up. skill fixes three mechanisms: **canonical arc** brand (one written narrative spine: world's change, old game villain, customer-hero, brand-as-guide, stakes, promised land), **chapters discipline** (every campaign positions chapter *of arc* advancing it, never contradicting it, never off-arc), **continuity ledger** registry told chapters, story never repeats itself breaks canon). weave's version pattern atlas lena run: arc file law; written arc, arc enforcement. · p=Two business problems, one mechanism. First, *memory*: audiences forget disconnected campaigns remember stories continue chapter inherits meaning chapters before it, which compounding attention instead rented attention. Second, *coherence volume*: pulse posts daily pixel produces batches, way output stays one brand instead content mill story spine everything maps back to. small business difference between "that company posts stuff" "that story I'm following." · wu=Triggers: "campaign story," "narrative angle," "what's story here," "does fit our story," creating revising brand's arc, automatically whenever muse's concepts, lena's campaigns, pulse's content series need narrative positioning spark's third gate reference (arc fit). for: individual story *craft* (hooks, five-second moments, dinner-test delivery that's sibling `brand-storytelling` skill), wording (lena). · st:/ Protocol=`Load the brand's arc (configured path) \· -> If none exists: STOP — build it via assets/story-arc-template.md from the operator's \· real history and positioning (never invent a founding story or fabricate stakes) \· -> For any campaign/content: position it as a chapter \· — which arc element does it advance? (world-change / villain / hero's struggle /` · h3:Phase Load Build Arc=Read arc `story_arc_path` (weave's config, one brand). none exists, stop